title: H.S. cross-country: Indian Hills boys, girls win in Rhode Island
text:
Print 
Fresh off impressive victories Thursday at the Big North Freedom Division meet, the Indian Hills boys team and Julia Guerra of the Indian Hills girls team scored their second wins in three days Saturday at the Brown University Northeast Invitational at Goddard Park East in East Greenwich, R.I. 
The boys packed their top-five runners within 28 seconds from second to 12th places to win the Large School Varsity race over St. John the Baptist (N.Y.). Senior Matt Cohane took second in 15:40.76 for the 5,000-meter course. Chris Corcoran was fourth in 15:49.14 and Derek Barney seventh in 15:54.83. Sophomore Chris Leymeister ran 16:07.50 for 10th and Tom Holster completed the scoring in 12th, running 16:09.23. 
Guerra took the girls race by about 40 meters in 17:46.80, her fastest time on any 5,000-meter course after becoming the first girl all season to break 19 minutes at Garret Mountain on Thursday. Indian Hills was a respectable 13th in the 25-team field.
